[
    {
        "text": "So the latest mathematical fact\ntaking the internet by",
        "start": 0.44,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "storm, well, you may\nhave seen it.",
        "start": 3.48,
        "duration": 2.26
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's check this out.",
        "start": 5.74,
        "duration": 0.915
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't know if you\nhave seen it.",
        "start": 6.655,
        "duration": 1.275
    },
    {
        "text": "It's been all over\nthe internet.",
        "start": 7.93,
        "duration": 1.31
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm going to take 1 divided\nby 998,001.",
        "start": 9.24,
        "duration": 8.15
    },
    {
        "text": "If you take that fraction, what\nyou get, if you do the",
        "start": 17.39,
        "duration": 4.23
    },
    {
        "text": "decimal for it, you get\nsomething rather remarkable.",
        "start": 21.62,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "You get every single\nthree-digit number.",
        "start": 24.5,
        "duration": 3.27
    },
    {
        "text": "It starts with 0 point,\nand it goes 0, 0, 0.",
        "start": 27.77,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "So that's 0.",
        "start": 31.69,
        "duration": 0.34
    },
    {
        "text": "And it goes 0, 0, 1.",
        "start": 32.03,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "There's 1.",
        "start": 34.34,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "0, 0, 2--",
        "start": 35.3,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "0, 0, 3--",
        "start": 37.62,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "0, 0, 4--",
        "start": 39.4,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "0, 0, 5.",
        "start": 41.26,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "And it will give you every\nsingle there-digit number",
        "start": 42.78,
        "duration": 5.39
    },
    {
        "text": "except for one.",
        "start": 48.17,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "It doesn't give you 998.",
        "start": 49.86,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "Every single three-digit\nnumber except 998.",
        "start": 52.6,
        "duration": 3.45
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so let's go on.",
        "start": 56.05,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "So it goes 6, 7, skip a few.",
        "start": 57.34,
        "duration": 2.9
    },
    {
        "text": "Then it'll go 9, 9, 6--",
        "start": 60.24,
        "duration": 3.707
    },
    {
        "text": "9, 9, 7.",
        "start": 63.947,
        "duration": 2.643
    },
    {
        "text": "There is no 998.",
        "start": 66.59,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "It goes 9, 9, 9, and then\nit starts again.",
        "start": 68.23,
        "duration": 3.455
    },
    {
        "text": "It'll go back to 0, 0, 0, and\nthen 0, 0, 1, and goes to",
        "start": 71.685,
        "duration": 5.905
    },
    {
        "text": "start again.",
        "start": 77.59,
        "duration": 0.72
    },
    {
        "text": "It repeats.",
        "start": 78.31,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "So, we had a lot of people email\nus about this, and one",
        "start": 84.44,
        "duration": 3.98
    },
    {
        "text": "of our favorite YouTubers,\nVsauce, gives us a little",
        "start": 88.42,
        "duration": 3.34
    },
    {
        "text": "shoutout and asked us\nabout it as well.",
        "start": 91.76,
        "duration": 2.27
    },
    {
        "text": "And so, we had to make\na video about this.",
        "start": 94.03,
        "duration": 3.23
    },
    {
        "text": "We have seen this before.",
        "start": 97.26,
        "duration": 1.1
    },
    {
        "text": "It's not as remarkable\nas you may think.",
        "start": 98.36,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "So this is a repeating\ndecimal.",
        "start": 101.24,
        "duration": 1.79
    },
    {
        "text": "For start, I want to show you\nthat this is part of a family",
        "start": 103.03,
        "duration": 3.5
    },
    {
        "text": "of similar facts.",
        "start": 106.53,
        "duration": 1.66
    },
    {
        "text": "So, one thing to notice\nis 998001.",
        "start": 108.19,
        "duration": 6.49
    },
    {
        "text": "This is actually 999 squared.",
        "start": 114.68,
        "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, this is why we've got a\nlittle family of facts here,",
        "start": 119.68,
        "duration": 2.87
    },
    {
        "text": "because if I took 1 over 9,801,\nthis is actually 1 over",
        "start": 122.55,
        "duration": 8.19
    },
    {
        "text": "99 squared.",
        "start": 130.74,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "Same sort of idea.",
        "start": 131.96,
        "duration": 0.89
    },
    {
        "text": "And what you would get are all\nthe numbers, all the two-digit",
        "start": 132.85,
        "duration": 5.58
    },
    {
        "text": "numbers for that.",
        "start": 138.43,
        "duration": 0.97
    },
    {
        "text": "So you would get 0.0001020304.",
        "start": 139.4,
        "duration": 6.18
    },
    {
        "text": "So it's the same idea.",
        "start": 145.58,
        "duration": 1.17
    },
    {
        "text": "You get all the two-digit\nnumbers except",
        "start": 146.75,
        "duration": 2.99
    },
    {
        "text": "for 98 in that case.",
        "start": 149.74,
        "duration": 2.97
    },
    {
        "text": "Very similar idea.",
        "start": 152.71,
        "duration": 1.05
    },
    {
        "text": "9998001.",
        "start": 153.76,
        "duration": 3.34
    },
    {
        "text": "It's the same sort of idea.",
        "start": 157.1,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Again, this is 1 over\n9999 squared.",
        "start": 158.26,
        "duration": 5.8
    },
    {
        "text": "And you get all the four-digit\nnumbers.",
        "start": 164.06,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "What about 1 over 9 squared?",
        "start": 166.76,
        "duration": 1.57
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, that's the one I really\nwant to show you, because we",
        "start": 168.33,
        "duration": 2.39
    },
    {
        "text": "wanted to make this\na bit simple, OK?",
        "start": 170.72,
        "duration": 1.63
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's not go straight into it.",
        "start": 172.35,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's take the simplest\nexample.",
        "start": 173.69,
        "duration": 1.88
    },
    {
        "text": "1 over 9 squared.",
        "start": 175.57,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "So, 1/81.",
        "start": 177.13,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "That's what we're going to look\nat, 1 over 9 squared.",
        "start": 179.14,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "And that will give you all\nthe one-digit numbers.",
        "start": 181.72,
        "duration": 3.02
    },
    {
        "text": "0.01234567.",
        "start": 184.74,
        "duration": 6.95
    },
    {
        "text": "It missed 8.",
        "start": 191.69,
        "duration": 2.15
    },
    {
        "text": "9, and then back to 0 again.",
        "start": 193.84,
        "duration": 2.41
    },
    {
        "text": "It repeats that pattern.",
        "start": 196.25,
        "duration": 1.79
    },
    {
        "text": "So, it's the same idea.",
        "start": 198.04,
        "duration": 2.15
    },
    {
        "text": "So, let's see if we can work out\nwhy this is true, and then",
        "start": 200.19,
        "duration": 3.4
    },
    {
        "text": "this idea will work for the\nother examples that",
        "start": 203.59,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "we've seen so far.",
        "start": 205.93,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Right.",
        "start": 208.25,
        "duration": 0.45
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you want another\npiece of paper?",
        "start": 208.7,
        "duration": 0.935
    },
    {
        "text": "I do need another\npiece of paper.",
        "start": 209.635,
        "duration": 0.935
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's get you more paper.",
        "start": 210.57,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "So, the easiest explanation for\nthis is that we could make",
        "start": 218.34,
        "duration": 3.49
    },
    {
        "text": "any repeating decimal that\nwe wanted to make.",
        "start": 221.83,
        "duration": 3.78
    },
    {
        "text": "So, if you wanted to\nmake, say, this.",
        "start": 225.61,
        "duration": 2.84
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's say it's going to start\nwith naught point, and let's",
        "start": 228.45,
        "duration": 2.17
    },
    {
        "text": "take some digits.",
        "start": 230.62,
        "duration": 0.74
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's call it a1, that's\nthe first digit.",
        "start": 231.36,
        "duration": 3.16
    },
    {
        "text": "a2, the second digit.",
        "start": 234.52,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "a3.",
        "start": 236.23,
        "duration": 1.01
    },
    {
        "text": "And let's say it's, I don't\nknow, n digits long.",
        "start": 237.24,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "And then it repeats, so you\nget the same thing.",
        "start": 240.24,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "It goes dot, dot, dot, and you\nget that repeated over and",
        "start": 241.94,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "over again.",
        "start": 244.25,
        "duration": 1.15
    },
    {
        "text": "You can make that\nquite easily.",
        "start": 245.4,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "All you have to do to make that\nis to take this little",
        "start": 246.96,
        "duration": 3.45
    },
    {
        "text": "sequence, a1, a2, a3, up to an,\nand divide it by the same",
        "start": 250.41,
        "duration": 8.29
    },
    {
        "text": "number of 9s.",
        "start": 258.7,
        "duration": 0.68
    },
    {
        "text": "You've got n nines here.",
        "start": 259.38,
        "duration": 2.269
    },
    {
        "text": "9, 9, 9, whatever\nnumber that is.",
        "start": 261.649,
        "duration": 3.131
    },
    {
        "text": "So those two things\nwould be equal.",
        "start": 264.78,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "For our example, then, for 1/81,\nwe wanted 0.012345679,",
        "start": 266.64,
        "duration": 11.206
    },
    {
        "text": "dot, dot, dot.",
        "start": 277.846,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "012345679 over 999999999.",
        "start": 280.326,
        "duration": 10.614
    },
    {
        "text": "And that would give you that\ndecimal representation, and",
        "start": 290.94,
        "duration": 4.02
    },
    {
        "text": "that does simplify.",
        "start": 294.96,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "That makes a nice 1/81.",
        "start": 296.26,
        "duration": 3.27
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, you could make any\nrepeating decimal using that",
        "start": 299.53,
        "duration": 4.18
    },
    {
        "text": "method, but there is something\nspecial about that, because it",
        "start": 303.71,
        "duration": 3.185
    },
    {
        "text": "simplifies so nicely.",
        "start": 306.895,
        "duration": 1.095
    },
    {
        "text": "It makes such a nice number.",
        "start": 307.99,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "So, not all fractions like this\nwould make a nice number,",
        "start": 309.58,
        "duration": 3.64
    },
    {
        "text": "so why is it so nice?",
        "start": 313.22,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "Let me try and show you that.",
        "start": 314.58,
        "duration": 2.055
    },
    {
        "text": "So here's a little formula.",
        "start": 316.635,
        "duration": 2.315
    },
    {
        "text": "If you study mathematics, here's\na little formula that",
        "start": 318.95,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "you will learn, perhaps\nat some point, anyway.",
        "start": 321.04,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Let me show you what it is.",
        "start": 323.2,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "A little expression.",
        "start": 324.68,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "It starts with 1 plus\n2x plus 3x squared",
        "start": 326.58,
        "duration": 7.08
    },
    {
        "text": "plus 4x cubed plus--",
        "start": 333.66,
        "duration": 3.18
    },
    {
        "text": "and that can go on\nforever, OK?",
        "start": 336.84,
        "duration": 1.61
    },
    {
        "text": "So imagine this little\nequation.",
        "start": 338.45,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, here's a little\ncool thing.",
        "start": 341.21,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "If your number x is\nless than 1--",
        "start": 342.77,
        "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
        "text": "in fact, this works for negative\nnumbers as well if",
        "start": 347.65,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "they're greater than minus 1.",
        "start": 350.29,
        "duration": 2.38
    },
    {
        "text": "What I'm saying is\nif the size--",
        "start": 352.67,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "and that symbol means the size\nof x-- if it's less than 1,",
        "start": 354.76,
        "duration": 3.26
    },
    {
        "text": "this actually really\nsimplifies to",
        "start": 358.02,
        "duration": 3.18
    },
    {
        "text": "something pretty cool.",
        "start": 361.2,
        "duration": 1.03
    },
    {
        "text": "It becomes 1 over 1\nminus x squared.",
        "start": 362.23,
        "duration": 5.81
    },
    {
        "text": "And isn't that cool?",
        "start": 368.04,
        "duration": 1.1
    },
    {
        "text": "That complicated thing that goes\non forever, actually if",
        "start": 369.14,
        "duration": 3.51
    },
    {
        "text": "your x is less than 1, it's the\nsame as that, will give",
        "start": 372.65,
        "duration": 4.67
    },
    {
        "text": "you the same answer.",
        "start": 377.32,
        "duration": 1.015
    },
    {
        "text": "That's pretty cool.",
        "start": 378.335,
        "duration": 0.875
    },
    {
        "text": "That's pretty cool, isn't it?",
        "start": 379.21,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "Right.",
        "start": 380.17,
        "duration": 0.39
    },
    {
        "text": "So, we're going to use this\nto work out our fraction.",
        "start": 380.56,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so if I let x equal\n1/10, what do I get?",
        "start": 385.2,
        "duration": 8.32
    },
    {
        "text": "On this side--",
        "start": 393.52,
        "duration": 1.97
    },
    {
        "text": "I think I'll write\nit as a column--",
        "start": 395.49,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "I get 1, 2x.",
        "start": 398.43,
        "duration": 2.185
    },
    {
        "text": "So two times 1/10, that's 0.2,\nand you add them together.",
        "start": 400.615,
        "duration": 5.885
    },
    {
        "text": "This one is 3x squared,\nwhich is 0.03.",
        "start": 406.5,
        "duration": 5.87
    },
    {
        "text": "Plus 4x cubed equals 0.004.",
        "start": 412.37,
        "duration": 4.51
    },
    {
        "text": "And you keep going,\ndot, dot, dot.",
        "start": 416.88,
        "duration": 1.27
    },
    {
        "text": "Keep going forever.",
        "start": 418.15,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "All this on the left\nis equal to--",
        "start": 419.51,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "on this side, if x is 1/10,\nwell, let's see.",
        "start": 422.11,
        "duration": 5.02
    },
    {
        "text": "1 minus 1/10 is 9/10 squared.",
        "start": 427.13,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "9/10 squared is 81/100.",
        "start": 431.85,
        "duration": 3.925
    },
    {
        "text": "And because it's 1 over that\nfraction, you flip it.",
        "start": 435.775,
        "duration": 4.295
    },
    {
        "text": "This is equal to 100/81.",
        "start": 440.07,
        "duration": 4.12
    },
    {
        "text": "So all this is 1.23456\nequals 100/81.",
        "start": 444.19,
        "duration": 7.54
    },
    {
        "text": "The one we're interested in\nwas actually just the same",
        "start": 451.73,
        "duration": 2.45
    },
    {
        "text": "thing, but just 100\ntimes smaller.",
        "start": 454.18,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "You just had to shift it across\na couple of places.",
        "start": 456.52,
        "duration": 2.26
    },
    {
        "text": "So that's why you've got\nsuch a neat, cool",
        "start": 458.78,
        "duration": 3.48
    },
    {
        "text": "fraction out of that.",
        "start": 462.26,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "Really simple.",
        "start": 464.16,
        "duration": 1.1
    },
    {
        "text": "But why is it missing the 8?",
        "start": 465.26,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, that's interesting.",
        "start": 467.27,
        "duration": 0.73
    },
    {
        "text": "Why is it missing the 8?",
        "start": 468.0,
        "duration": 0.67
    },
    {
        "text": "Check this out.",
        "start": 468.67,
        "duration": 0.64
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's go a few down.",
        "start": 469.31,
        "duration": 1.575
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's do the 8.",
        "start": 470.885,
        "duration": 2.115
    },
    {
        "text": "Naught point-- let me see,\nI'm going to need six",
        "start": 473.0,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "of those, then 8.",
        "start": 475.53,
        "duration": 3.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's do the next one.",
        "start": 478.69,
        "duration": 1.382
    },
    {
        "text": "Naught point seven more.",
        "start": 480.072,
        "duration": 4.418
    },
    {
        "text": "Then there's the 9.",
        "start": 484.49,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "And if I want to add 10,\nit's going to 0--",
        "start": 485.93,
        "duration": 3.35
    },
    {
        "text": "try again--",
        "start": 489.28,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "point.",
        "start": 490.36,
        "duration": 0.952
    },
    {
        "text": "Now 0000000--",
        "start": 491.312,
        "duration": 5.838
    },
    {
        "text": "now, I want to write 010 here,\nbut there is no symbol for 10.",
        "start": 497.15,
        "duration": 3.59
    },
    {
        "text": "I can't write 010.",
        "start": 500.74,
        "duration": 1.45
    },
    {
        "text": "I have to write 10, like that.",
        "start": 502.19,
        "duration": 2.95
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, if you add this all\ntogether, you just add up the",
        "start": 505.14,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "columns, just a column\nat a time, can you",
        "start": 507.48,
        "duration": 2.27
    },
    {
        "text": "see it carries on?",
        "start": 509.75,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "Like you learned at school,\nthis carries on.",
        "start": 511.33,
        "duration": 1.719
    },
    {
        "text": "So this 1 plus 9, the 9 turns\ninto a 10, so that carries on.",
        "start": 513.049,
        "duration": 5.171
    },
    {
        "text": "So you get 1 plus 8, and\nthat becomes a 9.",
        "start": 518.22,
        "duration": 3.344
    },
    {
        "text": "Your 8 becomes a 9.",
        "start": 521.564,
        "duration": 1.446
    },
    {
        "text": "Your missing 8 turns into\na 9 because of all",
        "start": 523.01,
        "duration": 2.75
    },
    {
        "text": "this carrying on.",
        "start": 525.76,
        "duration": 1.49
    },
    {
        "text": "So all this is like a\nrow of dominoes .",
        "start": 527.25,
        "duration": 2.68
    },
    {
        "text": "You get a carry on, carry\non, carry on.",
        "start": 529.93,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "Your 8 turns into a 9, it\ndisappears, and you get that",
        "start": 531.91,
        "duration": 3.94
    },
    {
        "text": "number we discovered.",
        "start": 535.85,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "And the same sort of idea will\nwork for all those other",
        "start": 538.38,
        "duration": 3.38
    },
    {
        "text": "fractions that we looked at.",
        "start": 541.76,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "So the 1/998,001 is\nthe same idea.",
        "start": 542.98,
        "duration": 5.885
    },
    {
        "text": "You can prove the same thing\nwith the same idea.",
        "start": 548.865,
        "duration": 2.185
    },
    {
        "text": "It's a cool fact, isn't it?",
        "start": 551.05,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "It's a cool, little fact.",
        "start": 552.59,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, I like the fact.",
        "start": 554.27,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "And it's not completely trivial,\nbut you can make any",
        "start": 555.85,
        "duration": 3.98
    },
    {
        "text": "repeating decimal that you want\nto make, so that's not",
        "start": 559.83,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "particularly remarkable.",
        "start": 562.07,
        "duration": 0.74
    },
    {
        "text": "Why has it suddenly gone\non the internet?",
        "start": 562.81,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": "Who knows?",
        "start": 565.3,
        "duration": 1.37
    },
    {
        "text": "You get these things\never now and again.",
        "start": 566.67,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "These things go viral.",
        "start": 568.41,
        "duration": 2.85
    },
    {
        "text": "Mathematicians can roll their\neyes and go, oh, no, not this.",
        "start": 571.26,
        "duration": 3.95
    },
    {
        "text": "Oh, you're boring.",
        "start": 575.21,
        "duration": 1.87
    },
    {
        "text": "But every now and again, for no\nreason as far as I can see,",
        "start": 577.08,
        "duration": 3.15
    },
    {
        "text": "you get this happening.",
        "start": 580.23,
        "duration": 1.25
    }
]